```

The `EnsureSuccessStatusCode()` method is a built-in method of the `HttpResponseMessage` class. It checks whether the HTTP response status code indicates success (i.e. Whether the status code is in the range of 200-299). If the status code indicates an error, the method throws a `HttpRequestException`. By calling this method, we can ensure that the response is successful before attempting to read its content, which can help prevent errors in our code.

